<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="78" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles melanarius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanarius">Probles melanarius</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Szépligeti">Szepligeti</normalizedToken>
, 1895 (= 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Porizon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Porizon erythrostomus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrostomus">Porizon erythrostomus</taxonomicName>
Gravenhorst, 1829).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="78">
The genus belongs to the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Tersilochus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tersilochus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tersilochus</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Horstmann 1981</bibRefCitation>
) by having the first metasomal segment with a furrow between the glymma and the ventral part of the postpetiole, and the propodeum usually has a basal area (rarely with basal keel). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Probles</taxonomicName>
differs from other genera in this genus-group by the well-developed foveate groove of the mesopleuron, which is more or less upcurved anteriorly, elongate thyridial depression, weakly curved hind tibial spurs, and simple tarsal claws. Additional characters for distinguishing 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Probles</taxonomicName>
from other Korean tersilochine genera are given in the key published in our previous paper (
<bibRefCitation author="Balueva, EN" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Research" pageId="9" pageNumber="86" pagination="151 - 161" title="Study on two unrecorded genera, Barycnemis Foerster and Phradis Foerster (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tersilochinae), from South Korea." url="10.1111/1748-5967.12018" volume="43" year="2013">Balueva et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
